Olympics are right around the corner so we decided to share our favorite Olympic moment.  Oscar Albeiro Figueroa had seen failure, sweat & tears but with enough grit those tears turned to tears of joy. He won the only men’s gold in the category for Colombia. 💯🏅💯.

#olympics #colombia #nevergiveup #oro #gold

Enjoy, Tommy! 🏄

'Beautiful Sunday' was written by Daniel Boone. A happy & beautiful Sunday to you all!
(Malinda Herman Official)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Good News Movement on July 30, 2021. May be an image of 6 people, people standing and text that says '"I am safe.| safe. am loved": Boy who survived horrific family massacre is adopted by detective who worked on case good news! MOVEMENT'.

node.text: Florida detective Mike Blair, of the Hillsborough County Sheriff’s Office, responded to a horrific crime scene in March 2018 – a man had killed his girlfriend and special needs daughter and critically injured his son. The 8-year-old son wasn't expected to make it but pulled through. The detective would frequently check up on the boy. The detective said his heart strings were pulled when the boy asked him, "will you watch a movie with me?"... Now that detective is his adoptive father to the now 12-year-old boy and the boy says he feels so loved by his adoptive parents and 6 siblings.

node.text: 18-year-old Sunisa 'Suni' Lee won the women's individual all around gym final on Thursday making her the first Hmong American to become an Olympic all around champion. "This is such a surreal moment. I just feel like I could have never been here ever. It doesn't even feel like real life," she said. She credits her devoted family for her success and considers her father a source of inspiration. 🙌🙌

node.text: FATHERLY LOVE (MICHIGAN): This past Saturday, Ray Lucas ran into the basement of his burning house to rescue his 18-month-old twin daughters Milan and Malaysia on sheer memory of where they were since he couldn't see. The twins had been at his home with Lucas' mother and sister during what authorities are calling an electrical fire. Lucas sustained serious burns to his face, eyes, neck and arms. The babies were transported to Children’s Hospital where both babies were admitted one in ICU with severe burns but both are expected to recover. Complete strangers online have raised well over $200,000 for the family.
